03/11/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Fatos Nano pledged on Tuesday (2 November) that the government would continue efforts to fight organised crime and trafficking.
During a meeting with US Ambassador Marcie Reis, he also discussed bilateral co-operation.
Nano said he appreciates the US role as a strategic partner in Albania's efforts towards Euro-Atlantic integration.
(ATA, Albanian TV - 02/11/04)
